# Read in HB data
activity_hb <- read_csv(here("data/clean/activity_hb.csv")) %>% 
  filter(admission_type == "All")

── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
cols(
  year = col_double(),
  hbr = col_character(),
  admission_type = col_character(),
  age_group = col_character(),
  sex = col_character(),
  diagnosis = col_character(),
  number_of_discharges = col_double(),
  crude_rate = col_double(),
  easr = col_double(),
  hb_name = col_character()
)
mortality_hb <- read_csv(here("data/clean/mortality_hb.csv"))

── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
cols(
  year = col_double(),
  hbr = col_character(),
  age_group = col_character(),
  sex = col_character(),
  diagnosis = col_character(),
  number_of_deaths = col_double(),
  crude_rate = col_double(),
  easr = col_double(),
  hb_name = col_character()
)
#Make Scotland activoty data into a tsibble
activity_ts_sco <- activity_hb %>% 
  filter(hb_name == "Scotland" 
         & sex != "All"
         & !age_group %in% c("under75 years", "All")
         & diagnosis == "Stroke")

activity_ts_sco <- as_tsibble(activity_ts_sco, key = c(age_group, sex), index = year)
activity_ts_sco
activity_ts_sco %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = year,
      y = number_of_discharges,
      colour = sex) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(~ age_group, scales = "free")


activity_ts_sco %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = year,
      y = crude_rate,
      colour = sex) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(~ age_group, scales = "free")

# Make Scotland mortality data into a tsibble
mortality_ts_sco <- mortality_hb %>% 
  filter(hb_name == "Scotland" 
         & sex != "All"
         & !age_group %in% c("under75 years", "All")
         & diagnosis == "Stroke")

mortality_ts_sco <- as_tsibble(mortality_ts_sco, key = c(age_group, sex), index = year)
mortality_ts_sco %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = year,
      y = number_of_deaths,
      colour = sex) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(~ age_group, scales = "free")

mortality_ts_sco %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = year,
      y = crude_rate,
      colour = sex) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(~ age_group, scales = "free")

fit <- mortality_ts_sco %>%
  model(
   ets = ETS(number_of_deaths),
   arima = ARIMA(number_of_deaths),
   lm = TSLM(number_of_deaths ~ trend() + season())
  )
8 errors (1 unique) encountered for lm
[8] contrasts can be applied only to factors with 2 or more levels
fit
forecast_1 <- fit %>%
  forecast(h = 20)
forecast_1
forecast_1 %>%
  autoplot(mortality_ts_sco) +
  ggtitle("Forecasts ") +
  xlab("Year") +
  guides(colour = guide_legend(title = "Forecast")) +
  facet_grid(~ sex)
